      • cloneResource

        @Nonnull
Resource cloneResource​(Resource resource)
        Clone the given resource and return it's deep copy.

        Don't forget about that the implementation of the given resource could be various, so you don't know whether the given resource is a plain resource or some kind of combined resource (more resources acting as one resource). The clone made by this method (if concrete implementation does not specify it differently) is a plain resource so the inner structure could be another then the structure of the given resource. Use this method only if you are sure that you want to get a plain resource.

        Parameters:
        resource - Resource to be clonned.
        Returns:
        deep copy of resource.
